<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6875719>
    dc:description "FIGURE 2. Callitriche mathezii. A. Known distribution in Morocco. B. Growing submerged in a pool south of Timahdite in April 2019, with well-developed, long-pedicellate fruit and yellow pollen. C. Almost entirely female plant from Oulmès. Photographs: © R.V. Lansdown." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/6875719/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6875723>
    dc:description "FIGURE 3. A. Fruit biometrics of C. mathezii at three sites (Akzou, Oulmès, and Jbel Hebri). B. Fruit from three sites: left—Akzou; middle—Oulmès; right—Jbel Hebri. Photographs: © R.V. Lansdown." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/6875723/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

